Description: API implementation standards for Gambit Chess

# API Design
- Follow REST principles for endpoint design
- Implement endpoints defined in section 10.1 of README
- Use proper HTTP verbs (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
- Include appropriate status codes
- Implement consistent URL structure

# Request Validation
- Validate all incoming requests
- Implement schema validation for request bodies
- Use middleware for common validation tasks
- Return descriptive error messages
- Implement proper input sanitization

# Response Formatting
- Use consistent response format
- Include appropriate metadata
- Implement proper error responses
- Use pagination for list endpoints
- Include relevant links for resource navigation

# Authentication & Security
- Implement proper authentication
- Use JWT or similar token authentication
- Apply rate limiting for API endpoints
- Validate permissions for protected resources
- Implement CORS configuration

# API Documentation
- Document all endpoints with JSDoc or OpenAPI
- Include request/response examples
- Document error responses
- Specify authentication requirements
- Note rate limits and other constraints

